Independent candidates held their first political rally in Nyeri county on Saturday and expressed confidence they will win on August 8. The candidates under the umbrella of the Kenya Alliance of Independent Candidates held a rally at Ihururu Stadium in Tetu.Kiambu Governor William Kabogo, Uasin Gishu governor aspirant Zedekiah Buzeki, Nakuru top seat hopeful John Mututho and Tetu MP Ndung&rsquo;u Gethenji led the group.They said the people must be given a chance to decide the leaders they want. Kabogo told off critics saying they are in the opposition. He said the group supports President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s reelection.